output.crosstab_text:
Among those who graduated ten years previously from first degree courses in all subjects and who were working during the 2021-22 tax year, Education was the most common industry for White and Mixed / Multiple ethnic groups ethnicity graduates, and Human health and social work activities was the most common industry for Black / African / Caribbean / Black British, Asian / Asian British, Other ethnic group and Unknown ethnicity graduates.The industry with the largest range in proportions was Human health and social work activities, where Black / African / Caribbean / Black British ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and White ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion.

The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Financial and insurance activities, where Mixed / Multiple ethnic groups ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (Â£63,900) and Black / African / Caribbean / Black British ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (Â£49,500). The group with the highest earnings was Mixed / Multiple ethnic groups ethnicity graduates who worked in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of Â£63,900).
